00:02:10.919 --> 00:02:16.559
want to go parallel processing, you want it just to be simple. It shouldn't bother

00:02:16.559 --> 00:02:23.839
your development. So let's consider this simple case. We have a vector of 20 elements. You

00:02:23.839 --> 00:02:30.559
want to call a function called slow on each of the elements. And what happens inside there

00:02:30.559 --> 00:02:36.199
is that R will basically step by step go through them. And if slow takes one minute to finish

00:02:36.199 --> 00:02:43.600
each time, this is going to take 20 minutes. And with the parallel package, we have the

00:02:43.600 --> 00:02:49.600
beautiful MCL apply, we heard in several talks now. And it looks very similar. So as a developer,

