it feels familiar. The only difference here, you need to specify how many cores you want

00:02:54.399 --> 00:02:55.880
to parallelize.

00:02:55.880 --> 00:03:03.279
So if you parallelize on two cores, what's going to happen inside, the data, the X, is

00:03:03.279 --> 00:03:08.839
going to split up into chunks and workers will be started and they will start working

00:03:08.839 --> 00:03:14.679
on this downstream. And since they're two working on the same task, it's going to finish

00:03:14.679 --> 00:03:20.960
sooner, about 10 minutes. So everything is done and everything is beautiful. And as we

