00:21:58.800 --> 00:22:03.199
Does it fork R processes like parallel, or what does it do on Windows?

00:22:03.199 --> 00:22:07.760
So that's a good question. So I didn't have to go for it. I have time to go for all details.

00:22:07.760 --> 00:22:11.680
Future package doesn't really do the backends. It's just leveraging the parallel package.

00:22:11.680 --> 00:22:18.119
So you have the option to use multi-core forking like MCL apply or the cluster, but these also

00:22:18.119 --> 00:22:24.160
allow you to do other things. So there's like a caller package. So there's a caller backend.

00:22:24.160 --> 00:22:29.239
So the future package tried to stay away from that, but it comes with a parallel package

00:22:29.239 --> 00:22:30.239
built in.

00:22:31.239 --> 00:22:32.239
Perfect. Thank you so much.

00:22:32.239 --> 00:22:33.239
Thank you very much.

